<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 5:59PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Floyd
and western Polk Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 558 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Cave Spring, or near
Forney, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Cedartown, Cave Spring and Etna.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
